The paper deals with reinforcement learning, specifically exploration in sparse reward environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of empowerment as an intrinsic reward signal and the estimation of mutual information using neural networks suggest that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed method to the game of Montezuma's Revenge suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
